                    "company": "Guldenregel",
                    "description": "My specialty (PhD) is learning and communication. I make a difference by applying neuroscientific insights and music in my work. Having 'engineering-roots' I look for elegant and innovative practical solutions. I tailor my contribution to the challenge at hand. So, I may switch from one role to another: communication trainer, lecturer, coach, researcher, advisor, musician or process facilitator when multi stakeholder learning is required.\n\nMy professional competences are rooted in my Ph.D. research on communication and interactive project design (Wageningen, 1996). I have an additional specialization in educational quality and cross cultural communication. The latter especially in a context of cooperation between the Netherlands and Belgium. Being a musician all my life, I recently took an interest in applying music to my trainings and lessons. \n\nOver the past 22 years, I have run my own business 'Guldenregel' and worked for over 40 different client organisations: universities, business schools, educational and consultancy organisations, multinational organisations, local and national government institutions. I am concerned with the 'gap' between research, education and companies. We should look upon it as one knowledge system. We could do much more to create a win-win-win!\n\nPeople's life stories inspire me. In the course of their life, as long as they keep learning, people will develop their uniqueness more and more. Life changing events - and how you deal with it - are especially important and influence your professional communication style.\n\nI have a passion for music and look for ways to make it part of the learning processes that I facilitate. I recently started a vlog about this (guldenregel.wordpress.com) and I am currently researching how to learn content through music.",
